> Scripting basics

bash scripting lets you automate tasks and extend SDG-OS with custom tooling.

### script structure

a bash script starts with a shebang:

#!/bin/bash
echo "hello world"

make it executable: chmod +x myscript.sh
run it: ./myscript.sh

### variables

name="world"
echo "hello $name"

### command substitution

result=$(ls)
echo "$result"

### arguments

echo "first arg: $1"
echo "all args: $@"
echo "arg count: $#"

### reading input

read -p "enter your name: " name
echo "hi $name"

### exit codes

command
if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
    echo "success"
else
    echo "failed"
fi

### useful commands for scripting

- grep — search text
- sed — replace text
- awk — process columns
- jq — parse JSON
- find — locate files
- xargs — build command lines
